Effective Date: 10 October 2024
1. Introduction
This Privacy Policy explains how Amadeus ("the Bot") collects, uses, and discloses information when you use it. By using the Bot, you agree to the data practices described in this policy.

2. Information Collection
The Bot may collect the following types of information when it is invited to a server and used:

    Usernames and Nicknames: The Bot interacts with users to modify or check usernames and nicknames as part of its functionality.
    Messages: The Bot may process certain commands and responses to facilitate the requested actions. We do not store the content of your messages.
    Server Information: The Bot may store certain server details (like server ID) in memory to provide the requested services but does not permanently store such information.

3. Information Usage
    Command Responses: The Bot processes usernames, nicknames, and server data to provide its services, such as setting reminders or modifying nicknames.
    Improvements: Collected data may be used to troubleshoot issues and improve the Botâ€™s functionality and user experience.

4. Information Sharing
    We do not sell, rent, or lease your personal data to third parties.
    The Bot does not share user information except as required to comply with legal obligations or requests by law enforcement.

5. Data Security
The Bot takes reasonable precautions to protect the information it processes. However, no method of transmission over the internet is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.

6. Data Retention
The Bot does not store personal data permanently. All information processed is used in real-time and discarded when no longer necessary for the requested action.

7. User Control and Rights
    Opt-Out: Users may remove the Bot from their servers at any time to stop the collection and processing of information.
    Server Admin Controls: Server admins can restrict the Bot's permissions if they wish to limit its functionalities.

8. Changes to the Privacy Policy
We may modify this Privacy Policy from time to time. Users are encouraged to periodically review this policy for any updates.

9. Contact
If you have questions regarding this Privacy Policy, please contact us at 1sogron1@gmail.com.
